casebody.data:
SKOLNICK v. KERNER, GOVERNOR OF ILLINOIS, et al. No. 1401,

Misc.

Decided May 15, 1967. Appellant pro se. William G. Clark, Attorney General of Illinois, and Richard A. Michael, Assistant Attorney General, for appellees. Per Curiam.

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed for want of a substantial federal question.
